/Courses/Web-Scraping/1.1-What-is-Web-Sc.title: What is Web Scraping ?
/Courses/Web-Scraping/1.1-What-is-Web-Sc.content:
Web Scraping Simply is Extracting Data from a website for Various needs.
Web Scraping, is also like a method of developing tools for efficiently extracting data from the website.

/Courses/Web-Scraping/1.2-How-Web-Scrapi.title: How Web Scraping Works
/Courses/Web-Scraping/1.2-How-Web-Scrapi.content:
There are Basically 4 steps in web scraping :
1. Send Request
2. Get Response
3. Select Data
4. Extract Data

![[image/How Web Scraping Works.png]]

When you send a request to a website URL, you receive a HTML Response. For Selecting data, you can use CSS selectors and XPath.

/Courses/Web-Scraping/2.1-Scrapy-Install.title: Scrapy Installation
/Courses/Web-Scraping/2.1-Scrapy-Install.content:
#### For Windows
1. Setup Virtual env. Manually
2. Setup in pycharm
3.  if s1 and 3 done pip install Scrapy

##### To Create a env 
1. open your terminal
2. Use cmd
```
python -m venv .\venv(current destination)
```

Visual Build Tools - [https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/](https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/)
if any error, use c++ from above
